text: Kigazytamakovo () is a rural locality (a village) in Mishkinsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 184 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 10 km from Mishkino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Kigazytamakovo
